function pix=dva2pix(dva, scr)% conversion of degree of visual angle into pixels.% inputs :%	dva         : x degrees of visual angle%	scr         : structure describing monitor characteristics. Minimal fields required are listed below%      .subDist	: viewing distance [mm]%      .width	: physical width of monitor [mm]%      .xres    : x resolution of monitor% distance between fixation point and target in pixelspix = tan(dva*pi/180) *  scr.subDist/(scr.width/scr.xres);